# Code Style

## Python version

- Python 3.11+

## Typing

- Use type hints on all public functions and method signatures.
- Prefer `Mapped[]` for SQLAlchemy model columns.

## Async

- API routes and DB access are async (`async def`, `AsyncSession`).
- Scheduler job wrappers may be sync; delegate to async services via `asyncio.run` or an async helper if needed.

## Modules

- One primary class or responsibility per file.
- Module docstring at top describing the file's single responsibility.

## Stubs

- Use `pass` or `raise NotImplementedError` in unimplemented stubs; do not add fake business logic.

## Logging

- Use structured logging from `app.core.logging`; no bare `print()` in application code.

## Configuration

- Read settings only via `app.core.config.settings`; never `os.getenv` in feature code.

## Errors

- Raise exceptions from `app.core.exceptions` for domain errors.
- Map domain errors to HTTP responses only in `api/` layer (when applicable).

## Formatting

- Line length 100 characters where practical.
- Double quotes for strings unless matching surrounding file style.
